relation.short: Path to building 1?
relation.long.desc:
Correct, if both conditions apply:
- the first segment of the path goes through the building
- The last segment of the path overlaps with the building and goes across it

relation.short: Path to building 1?
relation.long.desc:
Correct, if both conditions apply:
- the first segment of the path goes under the roof
- The last segment of the path is above the roof

relation.short: Path to building 2?
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the path comes through the building

relation.short: Path to building 2?
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the path comes through the openning in the top of the building

relation.short: Path to building 3?
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the path makes a left turn behind the building

relation.short: Path to building 3?
relation.long.desc: Correct, the path's height is in the top half part of the building

relation.short: Path to building 4?
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the path is to the right side of the building and does not cross/overlap it

relation.short: Path to building 4?
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the path's height is in the top half part of the building

relation.short: Path to building 5?
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the path goes between two towers

relation.short: Path to building 5?
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the path goes under the bridge of the building

relation.short: Path to building 6?
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the path makes 2 circles around the building

relation.short: Path to building 6?
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the path starts from the bottom and goes higher while circumnavigating the building

relation.short: Rhino to path? X (from left to right of the front of the first building)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the Rhino is inside the circle path segment that goes around building 6

relation.short: Y (front to back of the first building)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if Rhino is in between the front side of the circle path segment and building 6

relation.short: Z (height)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the Rhino is lower than all path lines that goes around building 6

relation.short: Sheep to path? X (from left to right of the front of the first building)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the Sheep is further left than the left turn segment that goes behind building 3

relation.short: Y (front to back of the first building)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if Sheep is closer to the front than the left turn segment that goes behind building 3

relation.short: Z (height)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if Sheep is on the same height(overlapped boundaries in the Z-direction) as the left turn segment that goes behind building 3

relation.short: Shark to path? X (from left to right of the front of the first building)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if Shark is further to the left than any part of the path

relation.short: Y (front to back of the first building)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the Shark is between the 2 turns at the beginning and at the end of building 4

relation.short: Z (height)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if Shark is higher than the path passing next to it.

relation.short: cat to path? X (from left to right of the front of the first building)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if Cat is between the first right turn of the path and the left turn of the path that goes out from building 2

relation.short: Y (front to back of the first building)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if Cat is further in the back than the path segment that goes through building 2.

relation.short: Z (height)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if Cat is on the same height(overlapped boundaries in the Z-direction) as the path segment that goes through of building 2.

relation.short: Trees to path? X (from left to right of the front of the first building)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the Tree is between two turns before and after building 5

relation.short: Y (front to back of the first building)
relation.long.desc: Correct, if the Tree is ca. as far in front as the path segment that goes through building 5

relation.short: Z (height)
